Create a detailed TO-DO LIST for implementing Authentication and Forgot Password 
for a Preschool Management System admin web application.

System Context:
- Roles: SUPER_ADMIN, ADMIN, TEACHER
- SUPER_ADMIN account is created once during system setup (no forgot password).
- ADMIN and TEACHER accounts are created by Super Admin with temporary credentials.
- Both ADMIN and TEACHER must change password and add email on first login.
- After first login, ADMIN and TEACHER can use email-based forgot password.
- No public registration.
- Same backend APIs must later support a mobile application.

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 1: DATABASE TASKS
--------------------------------------------------
1. Add required fields to users table:
   - username
   - password_hash
   - email (nullable initially)
   - role (SUPER_ADMIN, ADMIN, TEACHER)
   - status (ACTIVE, INACTIVE)
   - first_login (boolean)
   - reset_token (nullable)
   - reset_token_expiry (nullable)

2. Ensure passwords are stored using hashing (bcrypt or equivalent).

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 2: USER CREATION TASKS (SUPER ADMIN)
--------------------------------------------------
3. Implement Admin & Teacher account creation:
   - Generate temporary username.
   - Generate temporary password.
   - Store hashed password.
   - Set first_login = true.
   - Email is optional at creation.

4. Prevent Admin and Teacher from creating other users.

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 3: LOGIN TASKS
--------------------------------------------------
5. Create login API:
   - Allow login using username or email.
   - Validate password.
   - Block inactive users.

6. After successful login:
   - If first_login = true, redirect to First Login Setup page.
   - Otherwise, redirect to role-based dashboard.

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 4: FIRST LOGIN SETUP TASKS
--------------------------------------------------
7. Create First Login Setup page:
   - Require user to change password.
   - Require user to add email (mandatory).

8. On submit:
   - Hash new password.
   - Save email.
   - Set first_login = false.

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 5: FORGOT PASSWORD TASKS (ADMIN & TEACHER)
--------------------------------------------------
9. Add "Forgot Password?" link on login page.

10. Forgot Password Request:
    - User enters email.
    - Validate email exists.
    - Validate role is ADMIN or TEACHER.
    - Validate account is ACTIVE.
    - Generate secure reset token.
    - Set token expiry (e.g., 15 minutes).

11. Send reset email:
    - Include password reset link with token.
    - Show generic success message to user.

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 6: RESET PASSWORD TASKS
--------------------------------------------------
12. Reset Password Page:
    - Validate token.
    - Check token expiry.
    - Show new password form.

13. On reset submit:
    - Hash new password.
    - Clear reset_token and reset_token_expiry.
    - Allow login with new password.

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 7: ROLE & SECURITY RULES
--------------------------------------------------
14. Disable forgot password for SUPER_ADMIN.
15. Prevent token reuse.
16. Log password reset actions in audit log.

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 8: UI TASKS
--------------------------------------------------
17. Login page:
    - Username/Email field
    - Password field
    - Forgot Password link

18. Admin UI:
    - User list
    - Reset status indicators (optional)

--------------------------------------------------
SECTION 9: TESTING CHECKLIST
--------------------------------------------------
19. Test Admin first login flow.
20. Test Teacher first login flow.
21. Test forgot password via email.
22. Test expired token handling.
23. Test inactive user handling.
24. Ensure SUPER_ADMIN cannot use forgot password.

--------------------------------------------------
FINAL REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------
- Keep implementation simple and readable.
- Avoid OTP and SMS gateways.
- Ensure APIs can be reused by future mobile app.
- Follow role-based access strictly.